article.headline: Florida Atlantic 91, Troy 87
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. (AP) -- Derrick Simmons scored 12 points in about six minutes to spur Florida Atlantic to a 91-87 victory over the Troy Trojans Wednesday. Simmons also led his team in scoring with a career-high 21 points and four rebounds. Troy's Boo Ramsey was the high scorer of the night with 22 points. Coming out of Florida Atlantic's (4-5, 1-0 Sun Belt Conference) lead at halftime, Ramsey hit a 3-pointer at the 13:22 mark to give his team a 60-54 lead. The Owl's Carlos Monroe made two buckets in the last 54 seconds, the first at the 40 second mark coming after a Ramsey 3-pointer brought the Trojans (5-6, 0-1) within four. Monroe finished with 20 points. Florida Atlantic's Sammy Sharp and Cedric Jackson had 16 and 15 points respectively.
